1. Executive Summary

QUENNE v2.0 introduces a new class of infrastructure intelligence that unifies quantum-inspired optimization, neuromorphic control, and multi-agent AI into a single cognitive fabric capable of governing AI, data centers, cities, energy systems, and cloud infrastructure in real time.

⸻

2. The Global Infrastructure Crisis

Modern civilization is constrained by:
   •   energy instability
   •   fragile supply chains
   •   insecure AI
   •   exploding data center demand
   •   climate-driven volatility

AI systems today optimize tasks, not infrastructure.

⸻

3. The Limits of Current AI

Current AI:
   •   lacks real-time physical awareness
   •   has no energy or carbon context
   •   cannot govern safety-critical systems
   •   scales dangerously without control

We need governing intelligence, not just models.

⸻

4. The QUENNE Paradigm

QUENNE defines a new class of AI:

An intelligence fabric that governs systems instead of just predicting data.

It operates across:
   •   compute
   •   energy
   •   security
   •   cities
   •   and networks

